.TH "drm_dev_set_unique" 9 "drm_dev_set_unique" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_dev_set_unique \- Set the unique name of a DRM device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_dev_set_unique
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device of which to set the unique name
.IP "name" 12
unique name
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Sets the unique name of a DRM device using the specified string. This is
already done by \fBdrm_dev_init\fP, drivers should only override the default
unique name for backwards compatibility reasons.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success or a negative error code on failure.
